Being entrepreneur doesn't mean being the boss. Being entrepreneur means putting your clients and your employees as your bosses. 
That's the main thing I learned from today's introduction to business class.

And also i learned that business idea may popped out from a single and simple problem, but it needs hardwork and hardwill. What is the value of unspoken idea? You got to work for it, you got to make your dreams become reality by working for it. That's the way you put values on your dream. This world doesn't need dreamers who doesn't do a single thing about their dream. This world needs DREAMERS WHO DO.

What else do we need to make a business? A good co-founder of course. a co-founder who completes me, so we can work together to achieve our goals. And also we have to maintain our networks with people around us because your network is your net worth. And also, don't feel guilty for sacrificing what's yours in order to achieve your business goals, because it's normal to sacrifice something big in order to achieve something great. You just have to be persistent with your effort, don't make it useless by quitting before you achieve your goals. Remember that obstacles are around you but your goals are waiting for you on the finish line! 
And also i would like to say thank you so much for today's guest lecture @kenratriiswari for teaching and motivating us! May your business go bigger and greater kak! Glad to know and learn from you :)
[Erlin A. R. / 19716195]
